 control. Making the case for the complementarity of touch and technology, this book is a passionate plea to recover a tangible sense of community and the joys of life with others.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aSocial interaction. 0aTouch. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Phenomenology.2bisacsh  ahistory of touch.  aphilosophy of touch.  asocial interaction.  asocial media.  athe senses.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073907708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2021 Englishz978311075415508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2021z9783110753929oZDB-23-DPH40uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/kear1995240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231553179423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231553179/original  a978-3-11-073907-7  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075415-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-DPHb2021